A 34-year-old man was shot with an arrow and hacked to death by suspected cattle thieves in Nyakach, Kisumu county on Thursday.Wycliffe Ochieng&rsquo;, a father of four, was killed by the livestock thieves while on his way home from Sondu market.Philip Ochieng' said his brother's body was discovered in the morning further asking the police to arrest the perpetrators."The police must ensure the culprits are prosecuted so that we can live in peace. Most of them are known," he said.County police commander Titus Yoma said the man succumbed to serious injuries in his stomach.Yoma said the man was alone at the time the incident occurred."We have launched investigations into the matter and will apprehend the suspects," he said.